{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Of course, they did know they were-- that we were Jewish. and we knew that they were Gentiles because when they came up and down the stairs in their little uniforms, as the kids, boys and girls, or the adults having joined the party, it was incredibly intimidating.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You barely stuck your head out-- out of the-- the room you lived in, which is, interestingly enough, a peculiar situation as we know the United States.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we had to share bathrooms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "German apartments did not have private bathrooms.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Usually, when you lived in an apartment house, you had a landing, and the family from above and the family from below had to use the facilities on that landing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you actually had to wait till it was absolutely safe even to use the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The question-- the question that came up, of course, most often is what can you expect from your own neighbors?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Absolutely nothing.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You couldn't ask, and you wouldn't receive a copy of a newspaper.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You had no radio.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You were cut off from the world.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the only way that you could possibly get some information was a fairly common European, as well as a German, accommodation that newspapers were pasted on a wall.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And anybody who could not afford or who had no access to the newspaper, and if you didn't have the star at that time, you could go to the corner and read the daily newspaper to know what was going on, but you did it pretty fast because you just simply didn't spend much time outdoors.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1938-- it was then, also, the total elimination of any-- any trace of personal freedom.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was just absolutely nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
